  "prompt": "I'm sick of hearing about Trump, can I block these questions on my Quora feed?",
  "response": "Yes, you can customize your Quora feed to reduce or block questions about certain topics, including Donald Trump. Here are some steps you can follow:\n\n1. **Mute Topics**: You can mute topics related to Trump. Go to a question about Trump, click on the three dots (ellipsis) near the question, and then select \"Mute Topic.\" You can also search for topics like \"Donald Trump\" or \"U.S. Politics\" and mute them.\n\n2. **Block Keywords**: In your settings, you might be able to block questions containing specific keywords. Look for a section in your settings related to feed preferences or content filtering.\n\n3. **Manage Notifications**: If you're receiving notifications about Trump-related content, you can customize your notification settings to avoid these.\n\n4. **Follow Different Topics**: Start following topics that interest you more. This will help balance your feed with content you prefer.\n\n5. **Report Content**: If you believe the content is spam or violates Quora's policies, you can report it.\n\n6. **Use Browser Extensions**: Some browser extensions can help filter content based on keywords.\n\nThese steps should help you tailor your Quora experience to better match your interests.",
